cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper proposes a framework for deep learning in medical image analysis using $SE(2)$ group convolutions. The focus is on improving performance without the need for data augmentation, which is a common problem in computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which are a popular machine learning technique, so cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also introduces a new approach to encoding geometric structure into CNNs, which could be relevant to researchers in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper applies the proposed framework to three different medical imaging problems, which could be relevant to researchers in cs.MM (Multimedia).
